event.title: Brazilian Day Festival
event.description: The community will be able to become partners in support of missions and humanitarian efforts. The money raised from Brazilian Day is used to support missionaries and projects in the United States and around the world.

event.title: Indian Classical Music
event.description: Celebrating Mahatma Gandhi birth date with an afternoon of Indian Classical Music featuring Sitar (Arjun Verma), Sarod (Manik Khan), Violin (Raginder Momi), and Tabla (Nilanjan Chaudhuri).

event.title: Thrift Store Runway
event.description: On Friday, October 13th, Trim Tab Brewing Company will be filled with racks on racks on racks of the hautest couture from yesteryear. Sourced from the finest thrift stores in the Greater Birmingham Metropolitan Area, these clothes will meet an auspicious fate!

event.title: Tall Bike Joust V
event.description: Tall Bike Joust is BACK for the Fifth Year! Join us for an evening celebrating all forms of cycling in Birmingham. Beer! Bikes! Music! Friends! Dont miss it. $5 Presale Online or in the shop. $10 at the door.

event.title: Holy Youth, Taylor Hollingsworth, Merilee Chaliss
event.description: Holy Youth and Taylor Hollingsworth will perform special sets, and Merrilee Challiss will unveil new work. Also, DJ Sinkhole will be in the mix.

event.title: Free Guided History Hike
event.description: These hikes are led by Red Mountain Park Historian, Jeff, and Education Director, Shelby, to take you deep into the Park to learn more about the Park’s history from mining for the Civil War to World War II and all the way to where we are today.

event.title: Adia Victory
event.description: Adia Victoria live at the Syndicate Lounge. Ages 18+

event.title: Seasick Block Party
event.description: As a “Thank You” for all of the love and support we’ve received over the last four years, Seasick Records is throwing a party… And we’ve invited SUPERCHUNK!
